                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17850914-84-off419 t17850914-84-crimeloc421"></join>, a little before two; I did not know who took it; this is the handkerchief; there was the crowd.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17850914-84-person933">
                  ALEXANDER
                   SCOTT
               <interp inst="t17850914-84-person933" type="surname" value="SCOTT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850914-84-person933" type="given" value="ALEXANDER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850914-84-person933" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>A little before two last Thursday, in the afternoon, I was standing at the side of St. Andrew's door, I saw the boy next the prisoner and another at this gentleman's pocket; and I saw the prisoner, when he saw me, throw this handkerchief in the mud; I am sure he picks forty forty handkerchiefs in a week.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was going of an errand for my mother, I was never near the gentleman's pocket.</p>
               <p>How old are you? - About ten.</p>
               <p>Who employs you to do this? - Nobody; I go out with a basket with greens and turnips along with my father.</p>
               <p>
